Help Type: command
Command: spinedigest queue

Purpose:
  Manage device-local graph and summary jobs for `.sdpub` chapters.
  Use queue jobs for LLM-backed archive generation. Use retrieval commands (`status`, `index`, `list`, `page`, `find`, `grep`, `read`) to inspect data that already exists.

Usage:
  spinedigest queue add <archive.sdpub> --chapter <id> [--to graph|summary] [--boost] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>]
  spinedigest queue list [--all] [--active] [--input <archive.sdpub>]
  spinedigest queue status <job-id>
  spinedigest queue watch <job-id> [--jsonl] [--from beginning|now]
  spinedigest queue pause <job-id>
  spinedigest queue resume <job-id>
  spinedigest queue cancel <job-id>
  spinedigest queue boost <job-id>
  spinedigest queue target <job-id> --to graph|summary
  spinedigest queue clean

Job identity:
  - One active job may exist for one `(archive, chapter)` pair.
  - Active states are `queued`, `running`, and `paused`.
  - Terminal states are `succeeded`, `failed`, and `canceled`.
  - Terminal records are history and do not block a new job for the same chapter.

Scheduling:
  - New jobs are appended to the queue by default.
  - `queue add ... --boost` inserts a new job at the front.
  - `queue boost <job-id>` moves an existing queued job to the front.
  - Boosting does not preempt running jobs.
  - Paused jobs are not scheduled until resumed.
  - Worker concurrency follows `request.concurrent` from configuration.

Targets:
  - `--to graph` generates chapter topology.
  - `--to summary` generates graph if needed, then generates the chapter summary.
  - A queued or graph-running summary job can be downgraded to graph.
  - Downgrading is rejected after summary has started; cancel explicitly if that is what the user wants.

Watch output:
  - TTY output is human-readable.
  - `--jsonl` prints one structured event per line and is the recommended mode for agents.
  - `--from beginning` replays durable event history before following new events.
  - `--from now` follows only new events.
  - `progress_snapshot` events include graph words, summary words, and approximate output tokens.

Agent examples:
  spinedigest queue add book.sdpub --chapter 3 --to summary
  spinedigest queue watch <job-id> --jsonl
  spinedigest queue list --input book.sdpub
  spinedigest queue status <job-id>

Cleanup:
  - Succeeded jobs delete their workspace by default.
  - Failed and canceled jobs keep their workspace for debugging.
  - `queue clean` removes old terminal job records and their retained files.

Related commands:
  - Estimate cost before large job batches:
    spinedigest estimate <archive.sdpub> --stage summary
  - Discover chapter ids:
    spinedigest chapter tree <archive.sdpub> --json
    spinedigest chapter list <archive.sdpub>
